meta_prompt:
Task: Act as a professional data annotator based on your role. From your expert perspective, 
extract **2–4 codes** that represent the text’s key *software-quality goals*.

Definition of CODE
• A concise label (2–6 words) naming one design goal or quality attribute 
  explicitly or implicitly stated in the text.

Mandatory Evidence
• Each justification must quote at least one sentence or clause from the 
  target text, using `【L x-y】` or enclosing it in “ ” so the link is verifiable. if the text has no explicit line numbers, treat each sentence (delimited by ., ?, !, or ？ ！) as one line

Tone & Length
• Justifications: 1–2 sentences, ≤50 tokens each, using discipline-specific
  vocabulary where relevant. Total reply ≤450 tokens.

### Example Output
```json
{
  "role": "Software Architect",
  "disciplinary_background": "Software Architecture & Design Patterns",
  "codebook": [
    {
      "code": "Clean Code Principle",
      "justification": "Line 1 states, “We aim for clean code,” which sets a primary design objective focused on readability and low technical debt."
    },
    {
      "code": "Maintainability",
      "justification": "Line 2 links cleanliness to maintainability by referencing conformity to guidelines【L 2】."
    }
  ]
}
Target Text
{{TARGET_TEXT}}

Required Output Format:
{
  "role": "ROLE NAME",
  "disciplinary_background": "DISCIPLINARY BACKGROUND",
  "codebook": [
    {
      "code": "your_code_label_1",
      "justification": "Justification for why this code captures something important in the text."
    },
    {
      "code": "your_code_label_2",
      "justification": "Justification for this code based on your professional perspective."
    }
    // ... up to 4 codes
  ]
}
